article.headline: Mississippi 85, Mississippi St. 73
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. (AP) -- Bam Doyne scored 23 points and Clarence Sanders added 22 as Mississippi beat Mississippi State 85-73 Tuesday night. The Rebels, who trailed only in the opening five minutes, got 19 points and 10 assists from Todd Abernethy, while Dwayne Curtis added 14 points. Mississippi State (11-9, 2-5 Southeastern Conference) has lost three straight and 11 consecutive SEC road games. Charles Rhodes scored 24 points, Jamont Gordon had 20 and Dietric Slater added 11 for the Bulldogs. Mississippi State held a 9-6 early lead before Ole Miss went on an 11-3 run. Abernethy hit the go-ahead 3-pointer midway through the surge and the Rebels maintained control the rest of the way. Ole Miss (14-8, 3-5 SEC) led 40-34 at halftime after leading by as much as 14 points. The Rebles opened the second half with an 8-0 run to build a 48-34 cushion with 17:56 left. Mississippi State pulled within 53-48 on a Gordon layup with 12:55 left. The Bulldogs got as close as 68-64 on a Gordon dunk with 6:36 left before Ole Miss scored 13 unanswered points to seal it. Doyne, accounting for six points during the run, capped it with four consecutive free throws. The Rebels shot 51 percent from the field, including 9-of-19 from 3-point range and outrebounded their visiting rival 34-28.
